          <p><bold><italic>Barcrawl </italic>and <italic>bartab </italic>algorithms</bold>. Rectangles specify input and output. Diamonds designate filters applied to data. Barcodes (<italic>barcrawl</italic>) or sequences (<italic>bartab</italic>) that do not follow the outlined rules are discarded. Arrows diverging from the central flow chart represent analytic steps that the user can choose to skip.</p>
